definitions.definition: Which thing, event, circumstance, etc.: used in asking for the specification of an identity, quantity, quality, etc.
That which; those that; the thing(s) that.
examples: He knows what he wants and what to do to get it.
What is amazing is his boundless energy.
And, what' s even worse, I have to work on Sunday too.
What is astonishing, she doesn't want the job. - What ’s even more staggering, neither of her friends does either.
I will do what I can to help you.
What I'll do is, I'll phone you to let you know.

main_definition: ( interrogative ) Which thing, event, circumstance, etc.: used in asking for the specification of an identity, quantity, quality, etc.
secondary_definitions: ( fused relative ) That which; those that; the thing(s) that.
( fused relative ) Anything that; all that; whatever .
